There is no MAP_FAILED check between the mmap() call and
unlock_lock_check().  If mmap() fails for any reason (ENOMEM,
unrecognized flag on a kernel that predates MAP_DROPPABLE, etc.),
map holds MAP_FAILED (-1UL).  unlock_lock_check() then calls
is_vmflag_set() with that address, which calls seek_to_smaps_entry()
with -1UL.  That address has no smaps entry, so seek_to_smaps_entry()
closes the file and returns NULL.  Back in is_vmflag_set(), the
goto-out path then executes fclose(NULL), which is undefined
behaviour and crashes in practice.

test_mlock_droppable() does check for MAP_FAILED immediately after
mmap(); the same pattern should be applied here, e.g.:

